It is now time to turn our attention to the frequently

26
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:24,990
asked questions for this week.

27
00:01:24,990 --> 00:01:30,810
The first question is what are subsidiary management plans?

28
00:01:30,810 --> 00:01:34,710
Project management plans often include support documents,

29
00:01:34,710 --> 00:01:37,620
called subsidiary management plans,

30
00:01:37,620 --> 00:01:40,120
which include a communications management

31
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:45,330
plan, procurement plan, and quality management plan.

32
00:01:45,330 --> 00:01:49,540
The next question is linked to how you might manage people

33
00:01:49,540 --> 00:01:52,530
and events during this phase.

34
00:01:52,530 --> 00:01:56,520
The question is what is a milestone log?

35
00:01:56,520 --> 00:02:00,870
A milestone log is a document containing a set of milestones

36
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:03,660
that I included in your project.

37
00:02:03,660 --> 00:02:06,890
A milestone is a scheduled event signifying

38
00:02:06,890 --> 00:02:09,650
the completion of a major deliverable

39
00:02:09,650 --> 00:02:14,760
or a set of related deliverables in the project life cycle.

40
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:18,310
Typically, the project will be divided into five to 10

41
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:20,040
major milestones.

42
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:23,740
Each milestone has a deliverable and a completion date

43
00:02:23,740 --> 00:02:25,680
associated with it.

44
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:29,790
The final question for this week is are the quality processes,

45
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:32,100
and do I need to apply them?

46
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:34,350
This process has identified the quality

47
00:02:34,350 --> 00:02:37,690
standards and requirements applicable to the project

48
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:40,930
and how you might go about achieving them.

49
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:44,320
In other words, it identifies techniques and quality

50
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:46,720
assurance that will be used to check

51
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:50,140
that each deliverable has met the required quality

52
00:02:50,140 --> 00:02:51,890
expectations.

53
00:02:51,890 --> 00:02:54,070
You will need to apply quality processes

54
00:02:54,070 --> 00:02:57,070
for your project, especially where the projects are

55
00:02:57,070 --> 00:03:02,040
large and complex and external stakeholders are involved.

56
